    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The program is best suited for those comfortable with business investment risk. Unlike property-based Golden Visas, your capital is in companies or financial instruments, not real estate. The startup route in particular carries significant risk—but also potential upside if you choose well.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-6">
      Health insurance is mandatory for the visa and prudent long-term. Italy's public SSN is excellent once you're enrolled, but international coverage provides flexibility, faster access, and coverage during Schengen travel. Budget €150-450/month depending on your needs.
    </p>

